dcterms:description: The Atari Learning Environment (ALE) is a framework for developing and evaluating reinforcement learning agents using Atari 2600 games. It provides a standardized interface and a diverse set of games to test generalization and learning capabilities.

dcterms:description: MiniImagenet is a subset of the Imagenet dataset, specifically designed for few-shot learning tasks. It contains 100 classes with 600 images each, providing a benchmark for evaluating learning algorithms in low-data scenarios.
dcterms:title: MiniImagenet

dcterms:description: Imagenet is a large-scale hierarchical image database designed for visual recognition research. It contains millions of labeled images across thousands of categories, serving as a benchmark for various computer vision tasks.
dcterms:title: Imagenet

dcterms:description: The Penn Action Dataset consists of video clips with detailed annotations for various human actions. It provides a rich resource for understanding and recognizing actions in videos.
